    "description": "Free Humanoid Wheeled — sibling morphology to the Free Humanoid Platform (humanoid_bipedal). Targeted at the shoal dock-B service mission (urban stormwater outfalls, harbor docks, industrial discharge points). Wheeled differential-drive base + tower stand + bipedal upper body inherited verbatim. ~70 kg total system, 2 kWh battery, 30 kg sustained payload at extended reach, 1.5 m/s peak speed, 600x800x350 mm base footprint, 15-inch pneumatic drive wheels. Drive actuator: QDD direct-drive into wheel hub (corpus: mit-cheetah-2 / mjbots-moteus). Upper body actuator distribution inherited from bipedal sibling (corpus: honda-e0 harmonic-drive at shoulder/elbow, shadow-dexterous-hand tendon at wrist/hand, pisa-iit-softhand at synergy hand, mini-cheetah QDD at neck/waist). Safety supervisor: MathGround-style Simplex (corpus: sherman-simplex-architecture, control-barrier-functions) plus wheeled-specific invariants (slope-tilt, edge-proximity, low-battery-on-shore-power). Mission integration with shoal dock-B (cartridge-swap, waste-hopper, biology-reservoir handshake, water-utility EAM). All masses and inertias are scaffold placeholders — iterate against physical CAD before any build.",
